<TITLE> 4 killed in Satkhira road crash </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Satkhira, Jan 24 (bdnews24.com)  Four people were killed and around 50 others injured in a bus crash, after the driver lost control of the vehicle as a tyre burst, in Satkhira district on Sunday. Kaliganj police officer Zahidul Islam said a crowded bus smashed into a roadside tree at Hajampara in Kaliganj upazila at around 11am. Islam said most of the passengers of the bus, which was badly damaged, were injured. They were rushed to different hospitals and clinics at Sakhira, Kaliganj, Nalta, Devhata and Sakhipur, where four injured passengers succumbed to injuries. The dead included bus conductor Sirajul Islam, 40, and Bishnupada Dey, 55, of Moutala village in Kaliganj. Identities of the two others could not be immediately verified, police said.
